column119: he says his decision has nothing to do with the election and he told the Prime Minister about it in September. Mr Farrugia said that although the airline still faces a daunting task to become viable
column120: significant progress has been made and it is on the right course. He goes into detail on what the airline has been through
column121: and says that incentivising low cost airlines to compete against routes that Air Malta already covers (without any specific aid) is not the right strategy going forward. ..... incentivising low cost airlines to compete against routes that Air Malta already covers (without any specific aid) is not the right strategy going forward\" This could not happen with Air malta because they just would not have the capacity and be able to offer the low cost seats. However Air Malta is required to provide link connections to major Airport Hubs

column148: "summary": "Former Air Malta chairman Sonny Portelli has been reconfirmed chairman of the Malta Council for Economic and Social Development
column149: a position he has occupied since April 2007. Parliamentary Secretary Chris Said noted that Mr Portelli's reappointment was a sign that the government and the social partners had confidence in him."
column157: "summary": "Air Malta has appointed Nicholas Xuereb chief financial officer. He will be spearheading the airline's financial department and will be reporting directly to the CEO Peter Davies. In a statement
column158: the airline said Mr Xuereb's appointment continues the build up of talent at senior management levels which is required to turn around the airline's performance and create a sustainable national airline for Malta. Mr Xuereb joins Air Malta with extensive experience in the finance profession
column159: having worked with Trelleborg Sealing Solutions Malta as the finance director for over 12 years and before that with PriceWaterhouseCoopers."

column179: "summary": "Philip Saunders has been appointed Chief Commercial Officer at Air Malta and takes up his position with immediate effect. He is responsible for leading all commercial activity on a day-to-day basis and spearheading Air Malta's restructuring in these areas. The Cabin Service and Ground Handling departments will now form part of the Commercial Department
column180: in line with Air Malta's vision to deliver consistently excellent service
column181: tailored to the needs of the Maltese market and meeting the airline's commercial objectives. Philip Saunders joins Air Malta with a strong track record built up over 20 years in the industry
column182: with significant experience in turnaround situations. Air Malta CEO Peter Davies said: “This appointment represents another important step in our plans to turnaround Air Malta. Mr Saunders brings in-depth knowledge of the international airline business and will be responsible for defining the airline's commercial strategy by making Air Malta more customer centric. On taking up his appointment
column183: Mr Saunders said: “I am looking forward to facing the challenges ahead here at Air Malta and am certain that
column185: we can create a positive future for the airline

column118: "summary": "Air Malta chairman Louis Farrugia has announced he will step down in May. Writing in The Times
column119: he says his decision has nothing to do with the election and he told the Prime Minister about it in September. Mr Farrugia said that although the airline still faces a daunting task to become viable
column120: significant progress has been made and it is on the right course. He goes into detail on what the airline has been through
column121: and says that incentivising low cost airlines to compete against routes that Air Malta already covers (without any specific aid) is not the right strategy going forward. ..... incentivising low cost airlines to compete against routes that Air Malta already covers (without any specific aid) is not the right strategy going forward\" This could not happen with Air malta because they just would not have the capacity and be able to offer the low cost seats. However Air Malta is required to provide link connections to major Airport Hubs
column122: Something low cost do not do. However Air Malta is required to provide link connections to major Airport Hubs
column123: Something low cost do not do.......... Keeping other routes open is probably not financially worth it
column124: and ultimately will force it to come back to the government
column125: asking for more subsidies. \"incentivising low cost airlines to compete against routes that Air Malta already covers (without any specific aid) is not the right strategy going forward.\" says Air Malta Chairman. It make me realized that the PN haven't changed in the past 40 years
column126: as I remember very vividly when the British Forces where based in Malta
column127: every job the MOD Reaching the balance between protecting Air Malta or having Low Cost is a very difficult process. Air Malta has it
column129: including myself but they have had massive subsidies and it will take time for their cost cutting and restucture to pay off."
column148: "summary": "Former Air Malta chairman Sonny Portelli has been reconfirmed chairman of the Malta Council for Economic and Social Development
column149: a position he has occupied since April 2007. Parliamentary Secretary Chris Said noted that Mr Portelli's reappointment was a sign that the government and the social partners had confidence in him."
column157: "summary": "Air Malta has appointed Nicholas Xuereb chief financial officer. He will be spearheading the airline's financial department and will be reporting directly to the CEO Peter Davies. In a statement
column158: the airline said Mr Xuereb's appointment continues the build up of talent at senior management levels which is required to turn around the airline's performance and create a sustainable national airline for Malta. Mr Xuereb joins Air Malta with extensive experience in the finance profession
column159: having worked with Trelleborg Sealing Solutions Malta as the finance director for over 12 years and before that with PriceWaterhouseCoopers."

column179: "summary": "Philip Saunders has been appointed Chief Commercial Officer at Air Malta and takes up his position with immediate effect. He is responsible for leading all commercial activity on a day-to-day basis and spearheading Air Malta's restructuring in these areas. The Cabin Service and Ground Handling departments will now form part of the Commercial Department
column180: in line with Air Malta's vision to deliver consistently excellent service
column181: tailored to the needs of the Maltese market and meeting the airline's commercial objectives. Philip Saunders joins Air Malta with a strong track record built up over 20 years in the industry
column182: with significant experience in turnaround situations. Air Malta CEO Peter Davies said: “This appointment represents another important step in our plans to turnaround Air Malta. Mr Saunders brings in-depth knowledge of the international airline business and will be responsible for defining the airline's commercial strategy by making Air Malta more customer centric. On taking up his appointment
column183: Mr Saunders said: “I am looking forward to facing the challenges ahead here at Air Malta and am certain that
column185: we can create a positive future for the airline

column1152: "extraData": {"title": "Air Malta chairman to step down in May"
column1153: "summary": "Air Malta chairman Louis Farrugia has announced he will step down in May. Writing in The Times
column1154: he says his decision has nothing to do with the election and he told the Prime Minister about it in September. Mr Farrugia said that although the airline still faces a daunting task to become viable
column1155: significant progress has been made and it is on the right course. He goes into detail on what the airline has been through
column1156: and says that incentivising low cost airlines to compete against routes that Air Malta already covers (without any specific aid) is not the right strategy going forward. ..... incentivising low cost airlines to compete against routes that Air Malta already covers (without any specific aid) is not the right strategy going forward\" This could not happen with Air malta because they just would not have the capacity and be able to offer the low cost seats. However Air Malta is required to provide link connections to major Airport Hubs
column1157: Something low cost do not do. However Air Malta is required to provide link connections to major Airport Hubs
column1158: Something low cost do not do.......... Keeping other routes open is probably not financially worth it
column1159: and ultimately will force it to come back to the government
column1160: asking for more subsidies. \"incentivising low cost airlines to compete against routes that Air Malta already covers (without any specific aid) is not the right strategy going forward.\" says Air Malta Chairman. It make me realized that the PN haven't changed in the past 40 years
column1161: as I remember very vividly when the British Forces where based in Malta
column1162: every job the MOD Reaching the balance between protecting Air Malta or having Low Cost is a very difficult process. Air Malta has it
column1164: including myself but they have had massive subsidies and it will take time for their cost cutting and restucture to pay off."
column1186: "summary": "Former Air Malta chairman Sonny Portelli has been reconfirmed chairman of the Malta Council for Economic and Social Development
column1187: a position he has occupied since April 2007. Parliamentary Secretary Chris Said noted that Mr Portelli's reappointment was a sign that the government and the social partners had confidence in him."
column1198: "summary": "Air Malta has appointed Nicholas Xuereb chief financial officer. He will be spearheading the airline's financial department and will be reporting directly to the CEO Peter Davies. In a statement
column1199: the airline said Mr Xuereb's appointment continues the build up of talent at senior management levels which is required to turn around the airline's performance and create a sustainable national airline for Malta. Mr Xuereb joins Air Malta with extensive experience in the finance profession
column1200: having worked with Trelleborg Sealing Solutions Malta as the finance director for over 12 years and before that with PriceWaterhouseCoopers."

column1224: "extraData": {"summary": "Philip Saunders has been appointed Chief Commercial Officer at Air Malta and takes up his position with immediate effect. He is responsible for leading all commercial activity on a day-to-day basis and spearheading Air Malta's restructuring in these areas. The Cabin Service and Ground Handling departments will now form part of the Commercial Department
column1225: in line with Air Malta's vision to deliver consistently excellent service
column1226: tailored to the needs of the Maltese market and meeting the airline's commercial objectives. Philip Saunders joins Air Malta with a strong track record built up over 20 years in the industry
column1227: with significant experience in turnaround situations. Air Malta CEO Peter Davies said: “This appointment represents another important step in our plans to turnaround Air Malta. Mr Saunders brings in-depth knowledge of the international airline business and will be responsible for defining the airline's commercial strategy by making Air Malta more customer centric. On taking up his appointment
column1228: Mr Saunders said: “I am looking forward to facing the challenges ahead here at Air Malta and am certain that
column1230: we can create a positive future for the airline
